description:
1.Understand the role of knowledge organization in information retrieval, access and other related processes;
2.Get familiar with cataloguing and indexing principles incorporating the concepts of subject analysis, classification, and metadata;
3.Acquire basic knowledge and skills in metadata standards and creation;
4.Understand the theories of thesaurus, ontology and authority file;
5.Suggest appropriate approaches to organizing knowledge in given situations 
6.Use basic techniques to organize and manage knowledge resources in digital and web-based environments.
